# Event context

This project is a hackathon prototype for the **Abu Dhabi AI PropTech Challenge**
("Building the Intelligence Layer for Land, Investment and Communities") — a
one-day event. Optimize every suggestion for **demo-by-tonight**, not production.

## What this codebase is

- Next.js 14 (App Router) + TypeScript + Tailwind dashboard.
- `app/page.tsx` sets the team's track: `land | investment | communities | decision`.
- `components/DemoPanel.tsx` is the demo heart: input → "Run Prototype" → AI output.
  The model hook is marked `CONNECT YOUR MODEL HERE`; by default a local mock in
  `lib/sampleData.ts` answers (no API keys).
- Real model calls belong in a route handler (`app/api/run/route.ts`) so keys stay
  server-side; keys go in `.env.local`, never in client code or commits.

## Event data

- Synthetic datasets, joinable on `district`:
  `sample_parcels`, `sample_investors`, `sample_transactions`, `sample_communities`, `districts` — plus `sample_listings` and `osm_amenities`.
- GitHub: https://github.com/abu-dhabi-ai-proptech-challenge/starter-kit/tree/main/data
- Hugging Face mirror: https://huggingface.co/datasets/eVoost/abu-dhabi-ai-proptech-challenge
- The data is synthetic — never present it as real Abu Dhabi market data.

## How to help this team win

- Bias toward the **single demo path working end to end**; cut scope before adding features.
- Keep components small and obvious — teammates must understand code they didn't write.
- When asked for a feature, prefer editing the existing structure over new abstractions.
- Suggest committing after each working step.
- Judging rewards: sharp problem framing, working prototype, AI doing real work
  (not decoration), demo readiness, and credible impact. 3-minute demo, strict.
